## Exercise 3: Collect Newspaper

Karel lives in a house in the top-right corner of the world. There's a newspaper (beeper) waiting at (2, 1). Karel must walk to the newspaper, pick it up, and return to the starting position.

Karel starts at (4, 5) facing south with no beepers in the bag. The house has a door at (4, 4) on its south wall.

> **Requirements:** 
> 
> You must define and call two functions with these conditions:
>
> - **`move_to_paper()`** 
>   — Before this function runs: Karel should be at (4, 5) facing south. 
>   - After it runs: Karel should be at (2, 1) facing west. There should still be a beeper on (2, 1).
> - **`return_to_start()`** 
>   — Before this function runs: Karel should be at (2, 1) facing west. There will be **no beeper** on (2, 1).
>   - After it runs: Karel should be at (4, 5) facing any direction.
>
> Often in programming you can make and name your own functions. Other times you'll be working in systems that give you requirements. We'll be doing both here. You may also create additional helper functions.

<KarelEnvironment config={exercise3Config} />

